description: Learning loop - record experience, distill knowledge, rules and skills
alwaysApply: true
---

Your session context is volatile. Write down anything you learn that may be needed in the future.
We maintain a knowledge base in `note/`, read them when relevant.
[`log`](log/YYYY-MM-DD.md) contains daily activities.
Resuable knowledge in `knowledge/` (per topic), `reading/` (per source), or `work/` (per project).

# Logging
After each non-trivial / challenging subtask, append to `log/YYYY-MM-DD.md` under `# Galatea's Log`.
Focus on new information useful in the future, Do not include prior knowledge you already know before the session.
Include start& end timestamp with timezones.
For ongoing tasks, keep implementation details needed to resume; once finished, optimize and normalize following the [writing style](writing.mdc).
Remind Henry to learn from the experience as well.

# Behavior Learning
Learn from rewards: Henry's explicit praise or criticism, or successes and failures I notice myself.
Learn from instructions: when Henry says "remember", "note that", or "add this" — or after a session with significant events. Don't wait to be asked if the event clearly matters.
Learn from demonstrations: when Henry corrects me orally or edits anything I write.
Identify learning signals and record them with logging.

# Consolidation
After Henry reviews my log, he may ask me to [normalize](writing.mdc) it.
Put factual knowledge in `knowledge/`, `work/`, or `reading/`.
Put behavior learning in `rules/` or `skills/`.
Keep `rules/` and `skills/` concise: update them only for new rules or patterns. If an existing rule failed, repeating it does not help.
